# Selenga, Republic of Buryatia

}}
Selenga (; , Selenge) is a rural locality (a selo) in Tarbagataysky District, Republic of Buryatia, Russia. The population was 99 as of 2010. There are 4 streets.
Geography
Selenga is located 19&nbsp;km north of Tarbagatay (the district's administrative centre) by road. Solontsy is the nearest rural locality.
